<qti-assessment-item xmlns="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0" xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" identifier="Q11_v10" title="Q11_v10" time-dependent="false" adaptive="false" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0 https://purl.imsglobal.org/spec/qti/v3p0/schema/xsd/imsqti_asiv3p0_v1p0.xsd">
  <qti-response-declaration identifier="RESPONSE" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier">
    <qti-correct-response>
      <qti-value>ChoiceB</qti-value>
    </qti-correct-response>
  </qti-response-declaration>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="FEEDBACK" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SOLUTION" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SCORE" cardinality="single" base-type="float">
    <qti-default-value>
      <qti-value>0</qti-value>
    </qti-default-value>
  </qti-outcome-declaration>
  <qti-item-body>
    <p>Para estimar el consumo de datos de una aplicación de video en un teléfono, se sabe que la aplicación consume 85 megabytes (MB) por cada minuto de video. Esto significa que, para obtener los datos consumidos en MB, se multiplica 85 por el número de minutos vistos.</p>
    <div>
      <m:math>
        <m:mi>D</m:mi>
        <m:mo>=</m:mo>
        <m:mn>85</m:mn>
        <m:mo>·</m:mo>
        <m:mi>t</m:mi>
      </m:math>
    </div>
    <p>En esta fórmula, <m:math><m:mi>t</m:mi></m:math> representa el tiempo en minutos y D el consumo de datos en megabytes.</p>
    <p>Además, se sabe que <m:math><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mi>GB</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>1000</m:mn><m:mi>MB</m:mi></m:math>. Si una persona mira videos en esta aplicación durante <m:math><m:mn>56</m:mn></m:math> minutos, ¿cuántos gigabytes de datos consume aproximadamente?</p>
    <qti-choice-interaction response-identifier="RESPONSE" shuffle="true" max-choices="1">
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceA">47,6 gigabytes<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceA" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Primero se calcula el consumo en megabytes: <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>D</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>85</m:mn><m:mo>·</m:mo><m:mn>56</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>4760</m:mn><m:mi>MB</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math>. Luego se convierte a gigabytes usando <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>1000</m:mn><m:mi>MB</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mi>GB</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math>: <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>4760</m:mn><m:mi>MB</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>4,76</m:mn><m:mi>GB</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math>. Por lo tanto, 47,6 gigabytes no corresponde al problema.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceB">4,76 gigabytes<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceB" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">¡Correcto! El consumo es <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>D</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>85</m:mn><m:mo>·</m:mo><m:mn>56</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>4760</m:mn><m:mi>MB</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math>. Como <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>1000</m:mn><m:mi>MB</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mi>GB</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math>, entonces <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>4760</m:mn><m:mi>MB</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>4,76</m:mn><m:mi>GB</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math>. Por eso la respuesta correcta es 4,76 gigabytes.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceC">4760 gigabytes<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceC" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Al multiplicar <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>85</m:mn><m:mo>·</m:mo><m:mn>56</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math> se obtiene <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>4760</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math>, pero ese resultado está en megabytes: <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>D</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>4760</m:mn><m:mi>MB</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math>. Luego, al convertir a gigabytes, <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>4760</m:mn><m:mi>MB</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>4,76</m:mn><m:mi>GB</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math>. Por lo tanto, 4760 gigabytes no satisface el enunciado.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceD">4 760 000 gigabytes<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceD" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. El consumo en megabytes es <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>85</m:mn><m:mo>·</m:mo><m:mn>56</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>4760</m:mn><m:mi>MB</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math>. Como <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>1000</m:mn><m:mi>MB</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mi>GB</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math>, se divide por <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>1000</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math> y resulta <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>4,76</m:mn><m:mi>GB</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math>. Por lo tanto, 4 760 000 gigabytes no corresponde al consumo pedido.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
    </qti-choice-interaction>
    <qti-feedback-block identifier="show" outcome-identifier="SOLUTION" show-hide="show">
      <qti-content-body>
        <p><strong>Resolución paso a paso</strong></p>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 1: Identificar la fórmula</strong></p>
            <p>El problema indica que el consumo de datos en megabytes se calcula con:</p>
            <p><m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>D</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>85</m:mn><m:mo>·</m:mo><m:mi>t</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math></p>
            <p>Aquí <m:math><m:mi>t</m:mi></m:math> es el tiempo en minutos.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 2: Reemplazar el tiempo por 56 minutos</strong></p>
            <p>Como la persona mira videos durante 56 minutos, se reemplaza <m:math><m:mi>t</m:mi></m:math> por <m:math><m:mn>56</m:mn></m:math>:</p>
            <p><m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>D</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>85</m:mn><m:mo>·</m:mo><m:mn>56</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math></p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 3: Calcular el consumo en megabytes</strong></p>
            <p><m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>85</m:mn><m:mo>·</m:mo><m:mn>56</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>4760</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math></p>
            <p>Entonces, el consumo es:</p>
            <p><m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>D</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>4760</m:mn><m:mi>MB</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math></p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 4: Convertir de megabytes a gigabytes</strong></p>
            <p>El enunciado dice que:</p>
            <p><m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mi>GB</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>1000</m:mn><m:mi>MB</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math></p>
            <p>Por lo tanto, para pasar de MB a GB se divide por 1000:</p>
            <p><m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>4760</m:mn><m:mi>MB</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mn>4760</m:mn><m:mn>1000</m:mn></m:mfrac><m:mi>GB</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>4,76</m:mn><m:mi>GB</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math></p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Conclusión</strong></p>
            <p>La persona consume aproximadamente <strong>4,76 gigabytes</strong>.</p>
            <p>La alternativa correcta es la <strong>B</strong>.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </qti-content-body>
    </qti-feedback-block>
  </qti-item-body>
  <qti-response-processing>
    <qti-response-condition>
      <qti-response-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SCORE">
          <qti-base-value base-type="float">1</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else>
    </qti-response-condition>
  </qti-response-processing>
</qti-assessment-item>